cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes secret sharing schemes and authentication schemes based on right-angled Artin groups. 
- cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics and Combinatorics) is also likely as the paper introduces new problems related to subgroup and group homomorphism in the context of right-angled Artin groups. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with algebraic structures and their properties. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of the word problem in right-angled Artin groups. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with decision problems related to group theory.
